<h2> Evening events </h2>


<ul>
<li><b>Research presentations: </b> Wednesday 13 April. <br>
<li><b>MGS dinner</b> Thursday 14 April. <br>
 </ul>


<h2>Registration</h2>

Registration includes coffee breaks and the workshop dinner on 14 April. <b>Registration has now closed.</b>
<h4> Early booking until 5 March </h4>

Student/academic rate £190 <br>
General rate £290 <br>
<i>If you are booking at the student/academic rate, please <a href="mailto:P.B.Levy@cs.bham.ac.uk">email me</a> either your website URL at your University, or a letter from your supervisor.</i>  <br>

<h4> Late booking until 24 March </h4>

Student/academic rate £360 <br>
General rate £460 <br>

<p>

<h2>Accommodation</h2>

We have reserved rooms until the end of February at the <a href="http://www.ibis.com/gb/hotel-5678-ibis-budget-birmingham-centre/index.shtml">Ibis Budget Hotel</a>, which is a short walk from Birmingham New Street station and a bus ride or  45-minute walk to the University.  

 The price is £225.50 for either a double room (one bed) or triple room (two beds) for 5 nights.  Breakfast is an extra £27.50 per person for 5 days.  Please quote confirmation number 651376 when booking.  <i>Also <a href="mailto:P.B.Levy@cs.bham.ac.uk">email me</a> to say that you have booked this, so that I can keep track.</i>




<h2>Location and Travel</h2>

<p>
Lectures are held in the Learning Centre (except on Wednesday), and coffee breaks are in the School of Computer Science.  Both are close to the University (Birmingham) railway station.  

    
</p>

<P>
    <h2> Restaurants </h2>

Lunch may be purchased at Staff House or at other outlets on campus.
  In the evenings, there are many restaurants near the University (on Bristol Road) and in the city centre.</a>

